description: Harrogate Town end a run of three consecutive home defeats as two own goals secure a comfortable 2-0 win over Cheltenham Town.
title: Harrogate Town 2-0 Cheltenham Town
title_page: Harrogate Town 2-0 Cheltenham Town - BBC Sport
maintext:
Harrogate Town have lost each of their prior three Football League games against Cheltenham Town, scoring just one goal in total across those matches.
Cheltenham Town are unbeaten across their last four league games against sides from Yorkshire (W1 D3) and will be looking to make that five unbeaten in such games for the first time since February 2014.
Harrogate have lost six of their last eight league games (W1 D1), though that sole victory in that time came last time out in a 2-0 victory over Barrow at Holker Street.
